    <text type="letter">  
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.02049_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Anderton, near Chorley.</name>
                    <name type="place">Lancashire, England.<ptr target="loc.04844_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1892-03-15">15 March 1892</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Just a line or two my dearest friend, my comrade &#38; father, dearest of all to my soul,
                to express the triumph &#38; joy &#38; cheer with which I think of you &#38; with which
                I receive tidings of you. Outwardly sad enough, but deep within my soul I know that all is well, 
                &#38; that our last words should be triumph &#38; praise.<ptr target="loc.02538_n4b"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.02050_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                Day by day I think of you with tenderest sympathy &#38; love. If only I could come for a
                moment to your bedside &#38; imprint upon your lips a long &#38; loving kiss. Be it as if 
                I <hi rend="underline">were</hi> with you,<ptr target="loc.04844_n2"/> &#38; here upon the paper I send you one as a 
                token of my dearest love</p> 
            <closer>
                <salute>X</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Wallace</hi></signed> 
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.02051_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
